 The evaluation was performed up to 150 MeV for 7 subsequent      2637 1451
 neutron emissions, 3 proton emissions and a single alpha-        2637 1451
 particle, deuteron, triton, and 3He for a total of 146           2637 1451
 residual nuclei. Only 5 of these were treated as exclusive,      2637 1451
 i.e., had an explicit reaction assigned to them along with the   2637 1451
 corresponding exclusive spectra for all particles and gammas.    2637 1451
 The exclusive reactions were (n,g), (n,elas), (n,inel), (n,      2637 1451
 2n), (n,p), and (n, 2p). For all the remaining we provide        2637 1451
 cross sections for residua production which represent a sum of   2637 1451
 contributions from all possible reactions populating a given     2637 1451
 residue. Their respective spectra are lumped together            2637 1451
 providing only seven cumulative spectra (for gammas, neutrons,   2637 1451
 protons, alphas, deuterons, tritons, and 3He) for all the        2637 1451
 inclusive channels.                                              2637 1451
